<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-29T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="1189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1189">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 EW/1–2345: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-29T13:00:00-04:00">January
                                    29, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>64. Reurtel 52, January 23. Please find an early opportunity to tell the
                            Foreign Minister that April may well be too late. Invitations will have
                            to go out some six weeks before conference<note n="38" xml:id="d1189fn38">United Nations Conference on International
                                Organization at San Francisco.</note> convenes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>